This paper deals with algorithms for maintaining a DFS tree in undirected graphs in a dynamic setting, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.Distributed). The paper also mentions parallel algorithms, which could fall under the category of parallel computing (cs.PF). The paper presents algorithms with near-optimal time complexity, which could fall under the category of algorithmic complexity theory (cs.DC). Finally, the paper mentions fault-tolerant DFS, which could fall under the category of fault-tolerant computing (cs.SI).
